      {
        "id": "64f48096c2200fe54da38996f345dd6c95c935cd",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 477,
          "name": "Jorge Hernandez",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "jorge.hernandez-herrero@att.com",
          "username": "jhh"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2020-03-11 18:55:43.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nI think we need to make a decision in the following:\n\n1. If we remove template.demo, it means that we won't have tests for VFC, CCVPN, etc .. which may be it's OK, as we don't actively support them, as well as the drl being supported?\n\n2. Should equivalent tests that are in template.demo be rewritten for frankfurt/usecases controllers?   If so, probably we could open a ticket on G release for it.\n\n3. There is no ONAP need to use drools-pdp using with the legacy mechanisms (using brmsgw).",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "7ca55fca347bf96bf704a58e7d02d09cce351b2c",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 477,
