        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2020-03-12 13:40:55.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> Patch Set 2:\n> \n> I think we need to make a decision in the following:\n> \n> 1. If we remove template.demo, it means that we won't have tests for VFC, CCVPN, etc .. which may be it's OK, as we don't actively support them, as well as the drl being supported?\n> \n> 2. Should equivalent tests that are in template.demo be rewritten for frankfurt/usecases controllers?   If so, probably we could open a ticket on G release for it.\n> \n> 3. There is no ONAP need to use drools-pdp using with the legacy mechanisms (using brmsgw).\n\n1. Yes it is ok to not have tests for individual actors such as VFC. CCVPN is a use case we don't support (per M1). Let's only have tests for Use Cases we support.\n\n2) Only rainy day is needed - open G Release ticket for the ones we don't get done. We'll attempt to get vFirewall enhanced to support Rainy day. The rest can go.\n\n3) Correct",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
